Description: Handle sliver at neck join of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Name Aischinas. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 130.46, where the tau in l.3 is not well preserved. It seems very probable that this is a piece drawn by Petrie (Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 21) and subsequently further damaged.
